<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 22 at 3:41AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...SLIPPERY SNOW COVERED ROADS THIS MORNING...
Some roads remain snow covered this morning as a result of last
night`s snowfall and temperatures below freezing. Temperatures
will only slowly rise above freezing by noon, but skies will
quickly clear after daybreak. The combination of warming
temperatures and clearing skies will help melt any lingering snow
by afternoon. Until then, drivers should be alert for slippery
roads and delay travel until later in the day if possible.</description>
